  "body": "## Motivation\r\nThere used to be confusion as to the value of `msg.*` when we implemented internal functions as call-to-self, so we disabled `msg.*` in internal functions in https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/issues/1199. However, since then internal functions are implemented just using JUMPs, so the EVM execution context doesn't change. In other words, `msg.sender` is the same no matter if it's used in an internal or external function, so we can lift this restriction.\r\n\r\n## References\r\n- #901\r\n- #1199\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
